' @id(USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE) <<added>> this cycle (0021)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE) <<added>> this cycle (0021)
' Cycle 0021 diff (current side): /mdd-deploy is inverted from
' guidance-only into a full EXECUTOR. Two gates are added — USE-DEPLOY-
' EXECUTE (walk the runbook to live traffic, pause only at irreversible
' steps, halt on error) and USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE (surface the full billing
' multi-factor gate before the live cutover). Nothing removed; Guide /
' Dialect / Purpose / AccessCheck / Inspect are reused.
title /mdd-deploy becomes an executor · cycle 0021 diff (current)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "PLAN then EXECUTE an Azure Container\nApps deployment: diagram + IaC +\nrunbook, then run it to live traffic" as Guide
  usecase "Choose & CONFIRM the IaC dialect\n(Bicep XOR Terraform)" as Dialect
  usecase "Confirm the deployment PURPOSE\n(dev/staging/prod)" as Purpose
  usecase "Account for who READS and WRITES\nevery secured store" as AccessCheck
  usecase "EXECUTE the runbook: manage auth,\ndry-run, apply, provision, migrate, route —\nautonomous except irreversible steps; halt on error" as Execute <<added>>
  usecase "CONFIRM go-live: surface the full\nproduction billing multi-factor gate\nbefore live-traffic cutover" as GoLive <<added>>
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Dialect
Op --> Purpose
Op --> AccessCheck
Op --> Execute
Op --> GoLive
Op --> Inspect

Guide ..> Dialect : <<include>>
Guide ..> Purpose : <<include>>
Guide ..> AccessCheck : <<include>>
Guide ..> Execute : <<include>>
Execute ..> GoLive : <<include>>
Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>
